Notes for the thesis table:
- k=2..6 regular counts reproduce the 2026-02 working-draft census EXACTLY
  (63/410/2072/8963/34108, every m-bucket) — the enumeration is stable.
- k=1 differs from the draft (18 vs 19): current canonical vc set for the
  core is 18 oriented types = 15 species + chiral splits of 3.3.4.12,
  3.4.4.6, 4.6.12 under rotation-only canonicalisation.
- Star counts differ from the draft (279 vs 328 vcs etc.): the current
  generator applies the in-ring N=24 scope (thesis sec:disc-scope); the
  draft's alphabet included off-ring stars (n=5,7,9,10,11).
- The 449 quoted at k=3 in results.tex is the SEED count (geometric builds
  of the 410 sets); wording fixed in the thesis accordingly.
